// ====================================================================
// OVERVIEW
// ====================================================================
// This file defines one or more Twitch bot users. At startup the bot:
//   1. Loads this file (path override via $TWITCH_CONF_FILE)
//   2. Normalizes channel names (lowercases, removes duplicates, strips '#')
//   3. Prompts for device authorization if access/refresh tokens missing
//   4. Persists newly obtained tokens back into this file
//   5. Launches one color-change bot per user
//
// Restart safe: writes are debounced/batched to minimize churn.

// ====================================================================
// AUTOMATIC TOKEN SETUP (RECOMMENDED)
// ====================================================================
// Provide: username, client_id, client_secret, channels.
// Leave access_token / refresh_token absent and the bot will guide you via a
// short-lived device code flow, then write tokens here automatically.

// ====================================================================
// MANUAL TOKEN SETUP (ALTERNATIVE)
// ====================================================================
// If you manually provision tokens (e.g., https://twitchtokengenerator.com)
// add:
//   "access_token": "your_access_token",
//   "refresh_token": "your_refresh_token",
// Required scopes: chat:read, user:manage:chat_color

// ====================================================================
// FIELD NOTES
// ====================================================================
// username            Twitch username (lowercased internally)
// client_id/secret    Required for device auth & token refresh (keep secret!)
// access_token        (Optional initially) created automatically if absent
// refresh_token       (Optional initially) created automatically if absent
// channels            Array of channel names (no '#', duplicates removed)
// is_prime_or_turbo   true if account has Prime/Turbo (color palette impact)
// enabled             Toggle to temporarily disable a user without removal

// ====================================================================
// SECURITY
// ====================================================================
// Treat this file as sensitive (contains secrets once populated). Avoid
// committing real valuesâ€”use the .sample as a template.
// Back up only to secure locations; consider file permissions (chmod 600).

